Name: Richat Structure
Description: This circular feature is located in the Sahara Desert of Mauritania. Also known as the "Eye of the Sahara", this feature is "thought to be caused by an uplifted dome that has been eroded to expose the originally flat rock layers".

Name: Salar De Uyuni
Description: Located in the Altiplano of Bolivia, the Salar de Uyuni is the largest salt flat in the world.

Name: Angel Falls
Description: Located in the Auyán Tepui of Venezuela, Angel Falls is "the tallest waterfall on land". Dropping "nearly 1,000 meters", Angel Falls is "9 times higher than Niagara Falls".

Name: Nanga Parbat
Description: While only the ninth tallest mountain in the world, Nanga Parbat has the tallest mountain face of any mountain at 4,600 ft from its base. Located in the Western Himalayas in Pakistan, Nanga Parbat is one of the most dangerous and deadly mountains to climb in the world, earning the nickname "Killer Mountain for its high number of climber fatalities".
